# Patch 0019 — Workspace state-history substrate (ADR 0006; Phase 2.5).
#
# The foundation research branching and time-travel consume: an append-only
# local store of point-in-time workspace snapshots, and raw material for the
# Phase 6 knowledge graph. KavachaSpaceHistory.sys.mjs owns
# kavacha-snapshots.sqlite in the profile (own file — snapshots are bulky
# and append-only wants indexed pruning; not a places side table).
#
# A snapshot captures ONE space: tabs as SessionStore.getTabState() strings
# (the exact serialization session restore round-trips — fidelity is what
# restart/unloader testing verified; TabStateFlusher runs first so
# scroll/form state is current), the active tab index, space identity
# metadata, and a COPY of the space's note (what you were thinking is the
# point; references would rot). Essentials excluded; pinned flagged.
#
# Triggers: space switch (outgoing space, fire-and-forget at the
# changeWorkspace chokepoint), archive (captured before tabs unload), quit
# (best-effort, no flush), and a "Snapshot This Space" palette command
# (registry, patch 0018). No interval timer — switch+quit bound staleness
# and a timer mostly makes dedup-discarded noise.
#
# Dedup: structural hash (ordered tab URLs + active index + note); volatile
# tab-state fields deliberately excluded or dedup would never fire.
# Retention: per-space count cap + age cap
# (kavacha.history.max-snapshots-per-space=100 /
#  kavacha.history.retention-days=90, GC after each write).
# Sync: local-only until Phase 5, same stance as notes.
#
# STAGING NOTE: the ZenSpaceManager hunks were generated surgically against
# the current upstream tip (the local dev checkout lags it) — whole-file
# copies would have reverted upstream's newest workspace fixes.
#
# Marionette-verified: manual snapshot inserts; identical structure dedups
# to null; structure change inserts again; space switch auto-snapshots the
# outgoing space (reason=switch); payload reads back versioned with
# parseable tab state; retention prunes to the cap; the palette shows
# "Snapshot This Space". Applies on top of 0018.
# Capture hygiene (2026-07-15): about:blank and dashboard-newtab tabs are
# skipped at capture — placeholder pages carry no work state and only
# added noise to timelines and branches (a 34-tab snapshot was mostly
# dashboards). Regenerated against upstream fcda16b.
